        <p>
            Find <m>f'(x)</m> using the limit definition of the derivative. Then evaluate at <m>x=-5</m>.
        </p>
        <me>
            f(x) = -\frac{1}{x^{2}}
        </me>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <me>
           f'(x) = \frac{2}{x^{3}}
        </me>
        <me> 
            f'(-5) = -\frac{2}{125}
        </me>
    </answer>
